	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>10 Minutes </strong> - 1 Mile Square - 7th Level (Illusion) - VS - 10 Days</p><br><p><strong>Illusory Image</strong></p><br><p>Roll an &amp;Reference[illusoryimages]{illusion check} for this spell.</p><ul><li><p>You reshape the appearance of natural terrain in an area up to 1 mile square. The terrain’s general shape remains the same, but you may make it look, sound, smell, and feel like a different type of terrain.</p></li><li><p>Examples: An open field or road could appear as a swamp, crevasse, or hills; a pond could look like a meadow; a precipice like a slope; or a rocky gully like a smooth road.</p></li><li><p>You may alter the appearance of structures or create illusory ones, but the spell does not disguise, conceal, or create creatures.</p></li><li><p>The illusion includes audible, visual, tactile, and olfactory elements. It can create illusory difficult terrain or make rough terrain seem smooth.</p></li><li><p>Any part of the illusory terrain removed from the spell’s area (such as a rock or stick) disappears immediately.</p></li><li><p>Creatures with &amp;reference[Truesight] see through the illusion to the terrain’s true form. However, they still perceive and can physically interact with the illusory elements.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
